  "detailed_description": "<h1>Gamepad is recommended</h1><p>Although this game supports keyboard and mouse input, it was designed with gamepad input in mind. Playing with gamepad is strongly recommended.</p><br><h1>About the Game</h1><i>...Have you ever seen these videos where neural networks learn to control physics-based characters?</i><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/20ae9ae48c0256589c9966a529c89517.poster.avif?t=1693942500\" width=616 height=346 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/20ae9ae48c0256589c9966a529c89517.webm?t=1693942500\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/20ae9ae48c0256589c9966a529c89517.mp4?t=1693942500\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >In <strong>LOCOMOTORICA: Staggering Ragdoll</strong>, <u>you</u> are the neural network.</h2><br><br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/818a6540949ff36462789c6d1ec143b5.avif?t=1693942500\" width=616 height=76 /></span><br>You are in control of an active ragdoll in a computer physics simulation. Move your legs manually with gamepad sticks and triggers to retain balance and walk.<br>You have various tasks to complete:<br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/fc5854ffd0e5f00261f73fc6b78449a5.poster.avif?t=1693942500\" width=616 height=346 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/fc5854ffd0e5f00261f73fc6b78449a5.webm?t=1693942500\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/fc5854ffd0e5f00261f73fc6b78449a5.mp4?t=1693942500\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><i>This game can be challenging at first, as it is partially inspired by QWOP, a 2008 game by Bennett Foddy. But if you get a feel for it, you can walk and navigate the environment with little effort, as demonstrated above.</i><br><br><i>(UPD: This game was made before Bennett Foddy announced \"Baby Steps\")</i><br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/1a865650d79a806ae1050aae66b986d8.avif?t=1693942500\" width=616 height=76 /></span><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Innovative character controls and physics<br></li><li>30+ challenging hand-crafted tasks<br></li><li>Endless procedurally generated levels<br></li><li>Steam Leaderboards with replays to race against<br></li><li>Level editor and Steam Workshop<br></li><li>Relaxing soundtrack</li></ul><br><br><i>From the creator of Drunken Wrestlers and Drunken Wrestlers 2.<br>Join my !</i>",
  "about_the_game": "<i>...Have you ever seen these videos where neural networks learn to control physics-based characters?</i><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/20ae9ae48c0256589c9966a529c89517.poster.avif?t=1693942500\" width=616 height=346 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/20ae9ae48c0256589c9966a529c89517.webm?t=1693942500\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/20ae9ae48c0256589c9966a529c89517.mp4?t=1693942500\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >In <strong>LOCOMOTORICA: Staggering Ragdoll</strong>, <u>you</u> are the neural network.</h2><br><br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/818a6540949ff36462789c6d1ec143b5.avif?t=1693942500\" width=616 height=76 /></span><br>You are in control of an active ragdoll in a computer physics simulation. Move your legs manually with gamepad sticks and triggers to retain balance and walk.<br>You have various tasks to complete:<br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/fc5854ffd0e5f00261f73fc6b78449a5.poster.avif?t=1693942500\" width=616 height=346 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/fc5854ffd0e5f00261f73fc6b78449a5.webm?t=1693942500\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/fc5854ffd0e5f00261f73fc6b78449a5.mp4?t=1693942500\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><i>This game can be challenging at first, as it is partially inspired by QWOP, a 2008 game by Bennett Foddy. But if you get a feel for it, you can walk and navigate the environment with little effort, as demonstrated above.</i><br><br><i>(UPD: This game was made before Bennett Foddy announced \"Baby Steps\")</i><br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1542630/extras/1a865650d79a806ae1050aae66b986d8.avif?t=1693942500\" width=616 height=76 /></span><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Innovative character controls and physics<br></li><li>30+ challenging hand-crafted tasks<br></li><li>Endless procedurally generated levels<br></li><li>Steam Leaderboards with replays to race against<br></li><li>Level editor and Steam Workshop<br></li><li>Relaxing soundtrack</li></ul><br><br><i>From the creator of Drunken Wrestlers and Drunken Wrestlers 2.<br>Join my !</i>",
